Foremost economist, entrepreneur and Philanthropist Mr. Tony Elumelu has enumerated Fiscal infrastructure, Government Policies and Regulations as some of the factors and challenges mitigating development in Nigeria and Africa as a whole.  The UBA Chairman and Tony Elumelu Foundation founder who described the population of the African continent as a challenge and as well an opportunity, urged investors and development partners to come over to Africa to support young budding entrepreneurs whom he described as vibrant youths intelligent and hungry to succeed; given a digital "enabling environment."  Our correspondent Victor Njoku quotes Elumelu as speaking on the sidelines of the ongoing IMF World Bank Spring Meetings in Washington DC as a member of a panel of discussants with the theme; "Digital economy for Africa".